replies.body:
@RH Venom 

I agree with all your points. The state of the game right now is worsening with every patch they give us. Damage is too high, games last 15-20 minutes, no room for counterplay if your team falls behind. This is ridiculous! We never asked for any of these! Plus they change the game waaaay too much during the season when preseason is supposed to be when huge changes occur. Now with almost every patch, huge changes are being shitted out by the awful balance and design teams. For example the scuttle crab change (WHICH NO ONE LIKED, LITERALLY NO ONE), the marksmen change (although I think it's a good thing they did this), and the reworks upon reworks. They are changing the game drastically with every patch, having it's players adapt constantly and not allowing them room to breathe. "We care more about our LCS viewers, than our playerbase," said Riot essentially. Super disappointing. 

We need someone to be hired to the balance team from the playerbase that actually cares. It's ridiculous how much suffering we have to go through all because of the esports scene and the neglect people from Riot have towards their own playerbase.

{{sticker:sg-shisa}}
